id using Test.jvmArgs. I’m going to dig deeper into this to clarify my understanding and ensure I’m following guidelines correctly. The nuances here are really interesting!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering exception handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how `ReflectUtils.defineClass` declares an Exception but doesn't catch `InvocationTarget`. This means that `Method.invoke` could throw an `InvocationTargetException` if it encounters an `UnsupportedFeatureError`. Since the underlying `Method.invoke` uses reflection, I wonder if this unsupported error could be wrapped in some way. I may need to catch the Exception and inspect its cause to handle this properly. It’s a bit tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JUnit testing options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about JUnit and how it operates. I could just write ReflectUtilsTest and change CglibTest to public, or maybe even delete CglibTest using bash. I wonder if bash file operations are acceptable; maybe I’ll skip that for now. It might be easier to edit CglibTest to be public and test Cglib, but that might not be necessary. The top-level has to be public, and I need to ensure the package is correct for my setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_REOZlnaY7YhxgsXxrBDfojy2|fc_05c6c6cae57215280169f6eba8384881919a4fc174cea2b426", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib/3.3.0/src/test/java/cglib/cglib/ReflectUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.ReflectUtils;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor;\nimport org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ReflectUtilsTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"cglib.cglib.ReflectUtilsGenerated\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_INTERNAL_NAME = GENERATED_CLASS_NAME.replace('.', '/');\n\n    @Test\n    void findsConstructorsAndMethodsFromStringDescriptors() {\n        Constructor<?> bytesConstructor = ReflectUtils.findConstructor(\"java.lang.String(byte[])\");\n        Method substringMethod = ReflectUtils.findMethod(\"String.substring(int)\");\n\n        assertThat(bytesConstructor.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        assertThat(bytesConstructor.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(byte[].class);\n        assertThat(substringMethod.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        assertThat(substringMethod.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(int.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInstancesFromDeclaredConstructors() {\n        Constructor<?> constructor = ReflectUtils.getConstructor(ConstructedValue.class, new Class[] { String.class });\n\n        ConstructedValue value = (ConstructedValue) ReflectUtils.newInstance(constructor, new Object[] { \"created\" });\n\n        assertThat(value.value()).isEqualTo(\"created\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void findsDeclaredMethodsAcrossTheClassHierarchy() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        Method method = ReflectUtils.findDeclaredMethod(MethodChild.class, \"describe\", new Class[] { String.class });\n\n        assertThat(method.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(MethodParent.class);\n        assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"describe\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void collectsDeclaredMethodsFromClassesAndInterfaces() {\n        List<Method> methods = ReflectUtils.addAllMethods(MethodChild.class, new ArrayList<>());\n\n        assertThat(methods)\n                .extracting(Method::getName)\n                .contains(\"childOnly\", \"describe\", \"fromInterface\", \"toString\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void findsTheSingleMethodDeclaredByAnInterface() {\n        Method method = ReflectUtils.findInterfaceMethod(SingleMethodFactory.class);\n\n        assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"newInstance\");\n        assertThat(method.getReturnType()).isEqualTo(ConstructedValue.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void definesClassAndInitializesIt() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Class<?> generatedClass = ReflectUtils.defineClass(\n                    GENERATED_CLASS_NAME,\n                    createGeneratedClassBytes(),\n                    ReflectUtilsTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n            assertThat(generatedClass.getName()).isEqualTo(GENERATED_CLASS_NAME);\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(exception.getCause());\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] createGeneratedClassBytes() {\n        ClassWriter classWriter = new ClassWriter(0);\n        classWriter.visit(\n                Opcodes.V1_8,\n                Opcodes.ACC_PUBLIC,\n                GENERATED_CLASS_INTERNAL_NAME,\n                null,\n                \"java/lang/Object\",\n                null);\n        MethodVisitor constructor = classWriter.visitMethod(Opcodes.ACC_PUBLIC, \"<init>\", \"()V\", null, null);\n        constructor.visitCode();\n        constructor.visitVarInsn(Opcodes.ALOAD, 0);\n        constructor.visitMethodInsn(Opcodes.INVOKESPECIAL, \"java/lang/Object\", \"<init>\", \"()V\", false);\n        constructor.visitInsn(Opcodes.RETURN);\n        constructor.visitMaxs(1, 1);\n        constructor.visitEnd();\n        classWriter.visitEnd();\n        return classWriter.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static void rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        if (throwable instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            return;\n        }\n        if (throwable instanceof RuntimeException runtimeException) {\n            throw runtimeException;\n        }\n        if (throwable instanceof Error error) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n        throw new IllegalStateException(throwable);\n    }\n\n    public static final class ConstructedValue {\n        private final String value;\n\n        private ConstructedValue(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n\n        public String value() {\n            return value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class MethodParent {\n        protected String describe(String input) {\n            return \"parent:\" + input;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public interface MethodContract {\n        String fromInterface();\n    }\n\n    public static final class MethodChild extends MethodParent implements MethodContract {\n        public String childOnly() {\n            return \"child\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String fromInterface() {\n            return \"interface\";\n        }\n    }\n\n    public interface SingleMethodFactory {\n        ConstructedValue newInstance(String value);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 989, "output": 2893, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36650, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777789840713, "responseId": "resp_05c6c6cae57215280169f6eb914acc8191aaf63edb03cd2d19"}}
